org.quackbot.dao.model

Interface AdminEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    GenericEntry

    public interface AdminEntry
extends GenericEntry
    Bean that holds all known Admin information. This is meant to be integrated with JPersist and the database. Only configure if going to add to database, otherwise let JPersist configure it.

    If this needs to be changed in database, call #updateDB()

    Author:
    Leon Blakey

      • getChannels

        Set<ChannelEntry> getChannels()
        The Channel object that the admin might be attached to. Can be null

        A null value indicates this isn't attached to a channel. The admin can either be server admin or global admin

        Note that this isn't mapped by JPersist, it is simply a convience method

        Returns:
        the channel

      • getServers

        Set<ServerEntry> getServers()
        The Server object that the admin might be attached to. Can be null

        A null value indicates the admin isn't attached to a server. They must be a global admin.

        Note that this isn't mapped by JPersist, it is simply a convience method

        Returns:
        the server
